2020}}\n<!--{{current sport|sport=pro wrestling|event=professional wrestling PPV}}-->\n{{Infobox Wrestling event\n|name       = Money in the Bank (2020)\n|image      = MITB2020poster.jpeg\n|caption    = Promotional poster featuring various [[List of WWE personnel|WWE wrestlers]]\n|tagline    = Climb the Corporate Ladder<ref name=MITBlocation>{{cite web|last=Tedesco|first=Mike|title=Money in the Bank Ladder Matches to take place at WWE Headquarters in Stamford|url=https://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/154148-money-in-the-bank-ladder-matches-to-take-place-at-wwe-headquarters-in-stamford/|work=WrestleView|date=April 17, 2020|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n|promotion  = [[WWE]]\n|brand      = [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]]<br>[[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]]\n|date       = May 10, 2020\n|date_aired = \n|attendance = 0{{efn|name=Attendance|The event will be held without a live audience due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States]].}}\n|venue      = [[Titan Towers|WWE Global Headquarters]]{{efn|The event's Money in the Bank ladder matches will take place at WWE's [[Titan Towers|global headquarters]] in [[Stamford, Connecticut]], while the venue of the remaining matches has not been announced.}}\n|city       = [[Stamford, Connecticut]]\n|wwenlast   = [[WrestleMania 36]]\n|wwennext   = \n|event      = [[WWE Money in the Bank|Money in the Bank]]\n|lastevent2 = [[Money in the Bank (2019)|2019]]\n|nextevent2 = \n}}\n'''Money in the Bank''' is an upcoming [[professional wrestling]] [[pay-per-view]] (PPV) and [[WWE Network]] [[List of WWE pay-per-view and WWE Network events|event]], produced by [[WWE]] for their [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] [[WWE brand extension|brand divisions]]. It is scheduled to take place on May 10, 2020. It will be the eleventh event under the [[WWE Money in the Bank|Money in the Bank]] chronology.\n\nThe event was originally scheduled to take place at the [[Royal Farms Arena]] in [[Baltimore]], [[Maryland]], but the venue canceled all shows that were to be held in May [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports|due to the]] [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]. WWE announced that the show's [[Money in the Bank ladder match|eponymous ladder matches]] would take place at its \"[[Titan Towers]]\" global headquarters building in [[Stamford, Connecticut]] with a new \"Corporate Ladder\" gimmick culminating on the facility's roof. WWE has not yet announced where the card's remaining matches will originate.\n\n== Production ==\n=== Background ===\n[[WWE Money in the Bank|Money in the Bank]] (MITB) is an annual [[gimmick]] pay-per-view produced by WWE since 2010 and generally held between May and July. The concept of the show comes from WWE's established [[Money in the Bank ladder match]], in which multiple wrestlers use [[Ladder match|ladders]] to retrieve a briefcase hanging above the ring. The briefcase contains a contract that guarantees the winner a match for a world championship of their choosing at any time within the next year. Since the [[Money in the Bank (2018)|2018 event]], both the men's and women's matches featured eight wrestlers, evenly divided between the [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] [[WWE brand extension|brands]]. For 2020, it was reduced to six wrestlers divided between the brands. Male wrestlers compete for a contract to grant them a match for either Raw's [[WWE Championship]] or SmackDown's [[WWE Universal Championship|Universal Championship]], while female wrestlers compete for a [[Raw Women's Championship]] or [[SmackDown Women's Championship]] match contract. 2020 will be the eleventh event in the Money in the Bank chronology.<ref name=\"2020event\"/>\n\n====Impact of the coronavirus pandemic====\nThe event was originally announced with [[Baltimore]]'s [[Royal Farms Arena]] as host.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lambert|first=Jeremy|title=WWE Money In The Bank 2020 Scheduled For May 10 In Baltimore, MD|url=https://www.fightful.com/wrestling/wwe-money-bank-2020-scheduled-may-10-baltimore-md|work=Fightful|access-date=March 2, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"2020event\">{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Mike|title=WWE MONEY IN THE BANK 2020 DETAILS|url=https://pwinsider.com/article/134349/wwe-money-in-the-bank-2020-details.html?p=1|work=PWInsider|access-date=March 2, 2020}}</ref> However, [[Maryland]] issued a [[stay at home order]] on March 30, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Maryland to Enact Stay-at-Home Order Monday as Coronavirus Cases Top 1,400|last=Barnes|first=Sophia|url=https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/maryland-governor-larry-hogan-latest-monday-march-30-coronavirus-outbreak-covid-19-stay-at-home-order/2258161/|work=NBC4 Washington|date=March 30, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref> Subsequently on April 9, the host venue cancelled the event due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], and began issuing refunds. WWE initially did not announce whether the event will still go on from a different location (such as the [[WWE Performance Center]] in [[Orlando]] where most WWE shows have been held since mid-March),<ref>{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Mike|title=WWE MONEY IN THE BANK WILL NOT TAKE PLACE IN BALTIMORE, ROYAL FARMS ARENA ANNOUNCES CANCELLATION|url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/135465/wwe-money-in-the-bank-will-not-take-place-in-baltimore-royal-farms-arena-announces-cancellation.html?p=1|work=PWInsider|date=April 9, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Wilen|first=Jerome|title=WWE Money in the Bank pay-per view canceled due to COVID-19 outbreak|url=https://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/153495-wwe-money-in-the-bank-pay-per-view-canceled-covid-19/|work=WrestleView|date=April 9, 2020|access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref> though the company did air an advertisement promoting Money in the Bank during the second half of [[WrestleMania 36]].<ref name=\"WM36Part2\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=WrestleMania 36 results: Powell\u2019s live review of Night Two featuring Brock Lesnar vs. Drew McIntyre for the WWE Championship, John Cena vs. \u201cThe Fiend\u201d Bray Wyatt in a Firefly Funhouse match, Edge vs. Randy Orton in a Last Man Standing match, Rhea Ripley vs. Charlotte Flair for the NXT Women\u2019s Championship|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/05/wrestlemania-36-results-powells-live-review-of-night-two-featuring-brock-lesnar-vs-drew-mcintyre-for-the-wwe-championship-john-cena-vs-the-fiend-bray-wyatt-in-a-firefly-funhouse-match/|work=Pro Wreslting Dot Net|date=April 5, 2020|accessdate=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe pandemic brought about a modification to the Money in the Bank ladder matches. During the April 17 episode of ''[[WWE SmackDown|SmackDown]]'', it was announced that the two Money in the Bank ladder matches would take place at WWE's [[Titan Towers|global headquarters]] in [[Stamford, Connecticut]]. A new \"[[Career ladder|Corporate Ladder]]\" gimmick was also added to the matches, in which the participants must travel from the ground floor of the building to the roof in order to locate the briefcase, which itself is suspended above a ring on the roof.<ref name=MITBlocation/><ref>{{cite web|title=WWE Superstars will climb the corporate ladder at WWE Money In The Bank|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/moneyinthebank/2020/article/money-in-the-bank-climb-the-corporate-ladder|work=WWE|date=April 17, 2020|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Storylines===\nThe show will include matches that result from scripted storylines, where wrestlers portray [[Face (professional wrestling)|heroes]], [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villains]], or [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Tweener|less distinguishable characters]] in scripted events that build tension and culminate in a wrestling match or series of matches. Results are predetermined by WWE's writers on the Raw and SmackDown brands,<ref name=\"HSW\">{{cite web|title=How Pro Wrestling Works|url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|last=Grabianowski|first=Ed|work=HowStuffWorks|publisher=[[Discovery Communications]]|access-date=March 5, 2012|url-status=live|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDla2zy5?url=http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm|archive-date=November 18, 2013|df=}}</ref><ref name=WWEnt>{{cite web|title=Live & Televised Entertainment|url=http://corporate.wwe.com/company/events.jsp|publisher=WWE|access-date=March 21, 2012|url-status=live|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5esskNFVE?url=http://corporate.wwe.com/company/events.jsp|archive-date=February 26, 2009|df=}}</ref> while storylines are produced on WWE's weekly television shows, ''[[Monday Night Raw]]'' and ''[[Friday Night SmackDown]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wwe-smackdown-live-usa-1201782569/|title=WWE's 'Smackdown' Will Move To Live Broadcast On USA (EXCLUSIVE)|last=Steinberg|first=Brian|date=May 25, 2016|website=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=May 25, 2016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526113045/http://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wwe-smackdown-live-usa-1201782569/|archive-date=May 26, 2016|df=}}</ref>\n\nAt [[Super ShowDown (2020)|Super ShowDown]], [[\"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt]] lost the [[WWE Universal Championship|Universal Championship]] to [[Bill Goldberg|Goldberg]],<ref name=\"SuperShowDown2020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WWE Super ShowDown results: Powell's live review of \"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt vs. Goldberg for the WWE Universal Championship, Brock Lesnar vs. Ricochet for the WWE Championship, Big E and Kofi Kingston vs. The Miz and John Morrison for the Smackdown Tag Titles|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/02/27/wwe-super-showdown-results-powells-live-review-of-the-fiend-bray-wyatt-vs-goldberg-for-the-wwe-universal-championship-brock-lesnar-vs-ricochet-for-the-wwe-championship-big-e-and-kofi-kingst/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref> who in turn lost the title to [[Braun Strowman]] during [[WrestleMania 36]] Part 1.<ref name=\"WM36Part1\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=WrestleMania 36 results: Powell's live review of night one featuring Goldberg vs. Braun Strowman for the WWE Universal Championship, Undertaker vs. AJ Styles in a Boneyard match, Becky Lynch vs. Shayna Baszler for the Raw Women's Championship, Seth Rollins vs. Kevin Owens|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/04/wrestlemania-36-results-powells-live-review-of-night-one-featuring-goldberg-vs-braun-strowman-for-the-wwe-universal-championship-undertaker-vs-aj-styles-in-a-boneyard-match-becky-lynch-vs-shay/|work=Pro Wreslting Dot Net|date=April 4, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> On the following episode of ''SmackDown'', Wyatt interrupted Strowman after his match and reminded Strowman that it was he who brought him to the WWE with his old [[The Wyatt Family|Wyatt Family]] stable. Wyatt then stated he wanted his title back and Strowman accepted the challenge, which was scheduled for Money in the Bank, though against Wyatt's normal self instead of The Fiend.<ref name=\"SmackDown04102020\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/10/4-10-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-braun-strowmans-first-appearance-as-wwe-universal-champion-alexa-bliss-and-nikki-cross-vs-the-kabuki-warriors-for-the-wwe-womens-tag/|title=4/10 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell\u2019s review of Braun Strowman\u2019s first appearance as WWE Universal Champion, Alexa Bliss and Nikki Cross vs. The Kabuki Warriors for the WWE Women\u2019s Tag Titles, WrestleMania 36 fallout|date=April 10, 2020|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\nQualifying matches for the women's Money in the Bank ladder match began on the April 13 episode of ''Raw''. [[Asuka (wrestler)|Asuka]], [[Shayna Baszler]], and [[Nia Jax]] qualified for the match by defeating [[Ruby Riott]], [[Sarah Logan]], and [[Kairi Sane]], respectively.<ref name=\"Raw04132020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=4/13 WWE Raw Results: Powell\u2019s live review of Drew McIntyre and Becky Lynch appearances, Money in the Bank qualifying matches featuring Asuka vs. Ruby Riott, Kairi Sane vs. Nia Jax, and Sarah Logan vs. Shayna Baszler|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/13/4-13-wwe-raw-results-powells-live-review-of-drew-mcintyre-and-becky-lynch-appearances-money-in-the-bank-qualifying-matches-featuring-asuka-vs-ruby-riott-kairi-sane-vs-nia-jax-and-sarah-logan-v/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref> On the April 17 episode of ''SmackDown'', [[Dana Brooke]] defeated [[Naomi (wrestler)|Naomi]] to qualify for the match.<ref name=\"SmackDown04172020\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=4/17 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell\u2019s review of The Miz vs. Jey Uso vs. Big E in a Triple Threat for the Smackdown Tag Titles, Daniel Bryan vs. Cesaro and Naomi vs. Dana Brooke in Money in the Bank qualifiers, Sasha Banks vs. Tamina|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/17/4-17-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-the-miz-vs-jey-uso-vs-big-e-in-a-triple-threat-for-the-smackdown-tag-titles-daniel-bryan-vs-cesaro-and-naomi-vs-dana-brooke-in-money-i/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=April 17, 2020|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\nQualifying matches for the men's Money in the Bank ladder match began on the April 17 episode of ''SmackDown''. [[Daniel Bryan]] defeated [[Cesaro (wrestler)|Cesaro]] to qualify for the match.<ref name=\"SmackDown04172020\"/>\n\nDuring WrestleMania 36 Part 2, [[Tamina Snuka|Tamina]] was eliminated first in the [[fatal five-way elimination match]] for the [[SmackDown Women's Championship]] due to all of the other competitors piling on top of her for the pin; [[Bayley (wrestler)|Bayley]] subsequently retained the title.<ref name=\"WM36Part2\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=WrestleMania 36 results: Powell\u2019s live review of Night Two featuring Brock Lesnar vs. Drew McIntyre for the WWE Championship, John Cena vs. \u201cThe Fiend\u201d Bray Wyatt in a Firefly Funhouse match, Edge vs. Randy Orton in a Last Man Standing match, Rhea Ripley vs. Charlotte Flair for the NXT Women\u2019s Championship|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2020/04/05/wrestlemania-36-results-powells-live-review-of-night-two-featuring-brock-lesnar-vs-drew-mcintyre-for-the-wwe-championship-john-cena-vs-the-fiend-bray-wyatt-in-a-firefly-funhouse-match/|work=Pro Wreslting Dot Net|date=April 5, 2020|accessdate=April 5, 2020}}</ref> On the following ''SmackDown'', Tamina pointed out the fact that Bayley nor any other competitor in that match actually beat her and challenged Bayley to a [[singles match]] for the championship. Bayley agreed if Tamina could defeat her friend [[Sasha Banks]],<ref name=\"SmackDown04102020\"/> which she did the following week to earn the title match at Money in the Bank.<ref name=\"SmackDown04172020\"/>\n\n== Matches ==\n<!-- Please do not add any matches you may have heard on the internet or during taping, without a reliable source, such as the company's official website or other reliable websites. -->\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|times  = \n|future = yes\n|match1 = [[Asuka (wrestler)|Asuka]] vs. [[Shayna Baszler]] vs. [[Nia Jax]] vs. [[Dana Brooke]] vs. [[Lacey Evans]] or [[Sasha Banks]] vs. [[TBD]]\n|stip1  = [[Money in the Bank ladder match]] for a [[Professional wrestling championship#Gender championships|women's championship]] match contract<ref>{{cite web|title=Women's Money in the Bank Ladder Match|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/moneyinthebank/2020/womens-money-in-the-bank-ladder-match|work=WWE|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref> \n|time1  = \n|match2 = [[Daniel Bryan]] vs. [[Rey Mysterio]] or [[Buddy Murphy|Murphy]] vs. [[Aleister Black]] or [[Austin Theory]] vs. [[Apollo Crews]] or [[Montel Vontavious Porter|MVP]] 