0,000\">{{cite web|title=Nazi Loss in Poland Placed at 290,000 |website=The New York Times |year=1941 |url=http://www.freeimagehosting.net/image.php?cdbae543be.jpg |accessdate=16 January 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090207150102/http://www.freeimagehosting.net/image.php?cdbae543be.jpg |archivedate=7 February 2009 |df= }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"PN\">{{cite book | last = Peszke | first = Michael Alfred | authorlink = Michael Alfred Peszke | title = Poland's Navy, 1918\u20131945 | publisher=[[Hippocrene Books]] | date = February 1999 | isbn = 978-0-7818-0672-5| page = 37}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Poland's Holocaust: Ethnic Strife, Collaboration with Occupying Forces and Genocide...\">{{cite book |author=Tadeusz Piotrowski |title=Poland's Holocaust: Ethnic Strife, Collaboration with Occupying Forces and Genocide\u2026 |year=1998 |publisher=McFarland & Company |isbn=978-0-7864-0371-4 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=A4FlatJCro4C&pg=PA295&lpg=PA295&dq=1939+Soviet+citizenship+Poland | via=Google Books |author-link=Tadeusz Piotrowski (sociologist) }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Polish War, German Losses\">{{cite news|title=Polish War, German Losses |newspaper=The Canberra Times |date=13 October 1939 |url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/2513833|accessdate=17 January 2009 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">Seidner, ''Marshal Edward \u015amig\u0142y-Rydz Rydz and the defence of Poland'', p. 312</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ReferenceB\">''Wojna Obronna Polski 1939'', p. 851</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ReferenceC\">KAMIL CYWINSKI, ''Waffen und Geheimwaffen des deutschen Heeres 1933\u20131945''</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"SCHULENBURG\">[http://avalon.law.yale.edu/20th_century/ns069.asp Telegram]: The German Ambassador in the Soviet Union, (Schulenburg) to the German Foreign Office. Moscow, 10 September 1939 \u2013 9:40 p.m. and [http://avalon.law.yale.edu/20th_century/ns073.asp Telegram 2]: he German Ambassador in the Soviet Union (Schulenburg) to the German Foreign Office. Moscow, 16 September 1939. Source: The Avalon Project at Yale Law School. Last. Retrieved 14 November 2006</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"SDtW\">{{cite book |title= Stalin's Drive to the West, 1938\u20131945 |last=Raack |first=Richard |year= 1995 |publisher=Stanford University Press |isbn=978-0-8047-2415-9 |page=58|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=pAdZMaWn8cIC&pg=PA58&dq|accessdate=2 November 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Sanford\">{{Harv|Sanford|2005|pp=20\u201324}}</ref>\n\n<!-- <ref name=\"Toppe397\">Andreas Toppe, Milit\u00e4r und Kriegsv\u00f6lkerrecht: Rechtsnorm, Fachdiskurs und Kriegspraxis in Deutschland 1899\u20131940, Oldenbourg Wissenschaftsverlag, 2008, p. 397, {{ISBN|3-486-58206-2}}</ref> -->\n\n<ref name=\"Toppe398\">Andreas Toppe, Milit\u00e4r und Kriegsv\u00f6lkerrecht: Rechtsnorm, Fachdiskurs und Kriegspraxis in Deutschland 1899\u20131940, Oldenbourg Wissenschaftsverlag, 2008, p. 398, {{ISBN|3-486-58206-2}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"WIF2\">{{cite book |title=A World in Flames: A Short History of the Second World War |last=Kitchen |first=Martin |year=1990 |publisher=Longman |isbn=978-0-582-03408-2 |page=74|url=https://books.google.com/?id=0t-fAAAAMAAJ&q=%22The+joint+invasion+of+Poland+was+celebrated+with+a+parade+by+the+Wehrmacht+and+the+Red+Army+in+Brest+Litovsk%22&dq=%22The+joint+invasion+of+Poland+was+celebrated+with+a+parade+by+the+Wehrmacht+and+the+Red+Army+in+Brest+Litovsk%22|accessdate=2 November 2011 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"WIF\">{{cite book |title=Operatsiia Groza, Ili, Oshibka V Tretem Znake: Istoricheskaia Khronika|last=Bunich |first=Igor |authorlink= |year=1994 |publisher=VITA-OBLIK |location= |isbn=978-5-85976-003-9  |page=88 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"czoczer150\">{{Cite book | first = Andrew J. | last = Crozier | title = The causes of the Second World War | publisher=Wiley-Blackwell | year = 1997 | isbn = 978-0-631-18601-4 | url = https://books.google.com/?id=S2hBXzB7XaYC&pg=PA150&lpg=PA150&printsec=8&dq=anti-comintern+Poland | pages = 150