ukces\u00f3w |journal=[[Wprost]] |issue=1141 |date=10 October 2004 |language=Polish |accessdate=24 March 2005 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|authorlink=Dariusz Baliszewski |last=Baliszewski |first=Dariusz |url=http://www.wprost.pl/ar/?O=66711 |title=Most honoru |journal=[[Wprost]] |issue=1138 |date=19 September 2004 |language=Polish |accessdate=24 March 2005 |ref=harv |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070514184605/http://www.wprost.pl/ar/?O=66711 |archivedate=14 May 2007 |df= }}\n* {{cite book |last=Cooper |first=Matthew |title=The German Army 1939\u20131945: Its Political and Military Failure |publisher=Stein and Day |location=New York |year=1978 |isbn=978-0-8128-2468-1}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Corum |first=James S. |title=The Luftwaffe's Campaigns in Poland and the West 1939\u20131940: A Case Study of handling Innovation in Wartime |journal=Security and Defence Quarterly |date=2013 |volume=1 |issue=1 |pages=158\u2013189 |doi=10.35467/sdq/103158 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |authorlink=Marek Jan Chodakiewicz |last=Chodakiewicz |first=Marek Jan |title=Between Nazis and Soviets: Occupation Politics in Poland, 1939\u20131947 |publisher=Lexington Books |year=2004 | isbn=978-0-7391-0484-2}}\n* {{cite book |last=Ellis |first=John |title=Brute Force: Allied Strategy and Tactics in the Second World War |publisher=Viking Adult |edition=1st US |year=1999 |isbn= 978-0-670-80773-4|title-link=Brute Force (book) }}\n* {{cite journal |authorlink=Benjamin B. Fischer |last=Fischer |first=Benjamin B. |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/center-for-the-study-of-intelligence/csi-publications/csi-studies/studies/winter99-00/art6.html |title=The Katyn Controversy: Stalin's Killing Field |journal=Studies in Intelligence |date=Winter 1999\u20132000 |accessdate=10 December 2005 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Goldman | first = Stuart D. | title = Nomonhan, 1939; The Red Army's Victory That Shaped World War II | year = 2012 | publisher = [[Naval Institute Press]] | is